<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-22T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-22T19:00:00-05:00" n="455" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d455">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">851.00/2566: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador to the Polish Government in Exile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">at London</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-22T19:00:00-05:00">December
                                    22, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Polish Series No. 31. Your Polish Series 54, December 15, 7 p.m. You may
                            attend meeting as a guest, without, however, associating yourself with
                            the text of the Declaration. It is our understanding that that is the
                            basis for participation as proposed by the allied Governments
                            established in London and the basis on which the British Government has
                            agreed to take part.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>